# TallyBadger — where the rules live

Before planning or implementing substantive work, read:

- **[ARCH.md](../../ARCH.md)** — system shape, trust boundaries, main data flows, when to update architecture.
- **[STYLE.md](../../STYLE.md)** — coding standards, testing and delivery expectations, database/seed/snapshot/API contract rules, PR hygiene.

Do not duplicate long policy text in chat or in other rule files; keep changes to those two files when policy evolves. The **consistency checklist** for PRs lives in **STYLE.md** and in **[`.github/pull_request_template.md`](../../.github/pull_request_template.md)**.
